subSubSection.paragraph:
Head (
Figs. 58, 59, 62
): vertex, occiput, upper frons rugose punctate, punctures bearing short, appressed setae; sculpture along inner orbits with longitudinal rugulosity, central part of frons punctate; upper gena almost smooth, shining; LOL greater than OOL; occipital carina fine, complete, not distinctly crenulate; frons with strong median keel running slightly over half distance from interantennal process to median ocellus; striae of cheeks and face strong, reaching inner orbits; clypeus strongly transversely striate, anterolateral corners strongly projecting, with long erect setae; toruli contiguous with upper margin of clypeus; A 1 5.3 times as long as wide; A 2 2.7 times as long as wide; A 3 1.1 times as long as A 2 ; claval formula A 6 –A 12 / 2 - 2 - 2 - 2 - 2 - 2 - 1 .

